Re: Having problems specifing -datadir

Bitcointalk

2010-07-28 20:58:26 UTC - [11]Original Post

   It was able to reproduce this.  The database doesnʼt like the relative
   path.
   "bitcoind -datadir=./subdir getinfo" works against a running daemon,
   but trying to start the daemon as "bitcoind -datadir=./subdir" gets
   that exception.
   I guess we should resolve the full path before passing it to the
   database.
   It looks like you were the first one to ever use -datadir with a
   relative path.
